</IN>
<LP>
   FORT WORTH, Texas -- American Airlines, a unit of AMR
Corp., said its July traffic of 7.24 billion revenue
passenger miles was flat with year-earlier traffic. A revenue
passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one mile.
   The airline's July load factor, or the percentage of
available seats occupied, fell to 66.8% from 71.6%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first seven months of this year, American's
traffic rose 4.3% to 44.16 billion revenue passenger miles
from 42.32 billion miles a year earlier. The load factor
declined to 62.6% from 64.1%.
