                          MORTGAGE
                                                                                                       

   Federal National Mortgage Association -- $750 million
issue of Remic mortgage securities offered in 21 classes by
Bear Stearns &amp; Co. The offering, Series 1990-103, uses Fannie
Mae 9 1/2% securities backed by 30-year fixed-rate mortgages
as collateral. Price and yield data weren't immediately
available.
                                                                                                       

