   Credit Ratings
</HL>
<DATE>
08/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19
</SO>
<CO>
   UMM USBC
</CO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)
</IN>
<LP>
   UNITED MERCHANTS &amp; MANUFACTURERS Corp. (New York) --
Standard &amp; Poor's Corp. said it raised its rating on this
textile maker's subordinated debt, citing the company's
payment of interest arrears and its debt restructuring. S&amp;P
upgraded to double-C from D the rating on 13.75% senior
subordinated notes, due 2000, and 4% convertible subordinated
debentures, due in November. The rating concern also said
United Merchants' newly issued 3.5% senior subordinated
secured debentures, due 2009, are rated double-C. The new
debt was issued as part of the debt restructuring, in
exchange for a part of 13.75% and 15% debentures. About $170
million of debt is affected. Despite the debt restructuring,
a third bankruptcy-law filing is possible, because of
continuing poor operations, S&amp;P said. United Merchants'
viability remains questionable, without significant operating
improvements and asset sales, it said.
   ---
</LP>
<TEXT>
   U.S. BANCORP. (Portland, Ore.) -- Standard &amp; Poor's Corp.
said it lowered its ratings on $435 million of debt of this
bank holding company and its subsidiary banks, citing "steady
weakening of capitalization." The rating concern downgraded
senior debt to single-A from single-A-plus and subordinated
debt to single-A-minus from single-A, and affirmed the
single-A-1 rating on commercial paper.
</TEXT>
